name: The Original
description:
Lez take it back ... way back. 

Making it's mark in the early 1930s, Mona's in San Francisco, CA was one of the very first lesbian bars. Mona's Club 440 catered to an almost exclusively woman audience during World War II. Well known for being the place "Where Girls Will Be Boys" this was a place where many women  dressed in mens clothing.

Now lets make a toast to all your random bar hookups & long lasting loves.... Mona , this goes out to you!
